snippet.textDisplay: About a week ago some friends and I had a discussion for about an hour about just what defines a hole. We concluded that if the diameter of the opening is larger than the depth it is one hole and not two. So a straw would have two holes according to us. If it only have one opening it is a hole if the diameter is larger than the depth. If the diameter was smaller than the depth in a hole that is not a through hole it would be a so called “grop” in Swedish “pit” in English but I don’t find that this translation accurately represents what I mean. (Sorry if the grammar is bad. English is my second language)
